
A nicer terminal to use in windows... Cygwin with oh my zsh.

Oh-My-ZSH

1. cygwin Download: https://cygwin.com/install.html
note:[when ever you need to install new packages, run the installer again]
2. Run setup select following packages
  -zsh
  -git
  -nano
  -wget
3. Make ZSH default shell
```
nano ~/.bash_profile
```
add to top 
```
exec zsh
```
save in home/username.
Restart cygwin in zsh now.

Install oh my zsh
sh -c "$(wget https://raw.githubusercontent.com/robbyrussell/oh-my-zsh/master/tools/install.sh -O -)"

Solarized 
git clone https://github.com/karlin/mintty-colors-solarized.git ~/.solarized
echo 'source ~/.solarized/mintty-solarized-dark.sh' >> ~/.zshrc

Powerline fonts
https://github.com/powerline/font

